    "uid": "doi:10.2139/ssrn.6895958",
    "drop": false,
    "field": "finance",
    "role": "instrument",
    "bullets": [
      "97,028 consumer complaints filed with the US Consumer Financial Protection Bureau between January 2021 and December 2025 against eleven major consumer fintechs.",
      "A reasoning-capable large language model, family not stated, classified each complaint for reconciliation failure using chain-of-thought prompting, validated against 80 hand-labeled complaints at 88.75 percent accuracy and 0.88 F1.",
      "Reconciliation-related complaints closed with monetary relief at 9.96 percent versus 3.51 percent for other fintech payment complaints, a near threefold gap holding across all four product categories."
    ],
    "bullet_provenance": "ai",
